The paper deals with the Traveling Salesman Problem With Neighborhoods (TSPN) on uniform disks, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of the TSPN problem, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the derivation of bounds and approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the use of local structures and geometry to derive better bounds, which is a common theme in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
